fields.physical_description:
WEFT: white wool; Z2S; 15 threads per inch (58 per dm); depressed in places.

WEFT: cream wool; Z spun, unplied; usually 2 shoots after each row of knots but there are many places with 1 shoot of 2 parallel threads; varied but average of 12 knots per inch (50 per dm).

PILE: wool: 8 colours: red, yellow, dark blue, light blue, purple, dark brown, light brown, (difficult to distinguish; has probably faded from something else), cream; symmetrical knot tied around 2 threads; 90 knots per sq. inch (1450 per sq. dm).

SIDE FINISH: missing

END FINISH: missing

DESIGN: described as woven.  Field  light blue ground with long 5-sided panel in dark blue with stepped triangular niche at lower end.  From a small light blue vase within the niche grows a sprig with 5 star-like flowers.  The central blossom bears a further vase and sprig (9 vases in all).  These produce the effect of 3 floral rows.  At the very top of the panel are 5 similar but independent floral stars and on either side of the floral sprigs are 9 pairs of yellow ovals.  Outside the panel, the field is heavily decorated with bands of 10 or 9 and two halves of yellow bowls of three flowerheads outlined in red, purple or light brown.  These form a single column on either side of the panel and 2 bands along the upper edge.  There is a band beyond the field's lower edge, it contains 5 yellow and light blue stylised motifs, which could resemble sunburst or double-headed eagles; these are outlined in red on a purple ground.

BORDERS: There are ten, described from the inside:
(1) which also isolates and surrounds the lower panel: yellow ground with angular S-motifs, sometimes in pairs or triples, separated by a short diagonal bar.  In the upper part of the border there are 8 flowers and leaves, but some of the motifs are light brown and hard to see.

(2) yellow and light brown ground.  The lower part has a band of smaller and larger red triangles with light blue decoration.  They appear at the bottom of the side borders but then become a single row of light blue triangles outliend in dark brown and (along the top part) in dark blue.

(3), (5), (7), and (9): dark brown ground (small part in dark blue by accident) with a simple floral sprig.

(4), (6) and (8): same sprig on cream ground.
(10): incomplete; yellow ground with part of a multi-coloured pattern.
fields.dimensions: Length: 175.5 cm, Width: 112 cm, Weight: 14 kg
fields.production_note: A gift with 4 other rugs.  This "Kula" is one of three described as "good prayer rugs", 'Director.. you agreed we should accept these as a gift.  Your signature, Dorm. 9, please. GWD, June 1949'
